detaileddescription.para: Controls whether the catalog will cache table entries upon load.
If CACHE_EXPIRATION_INTERVAL_MS is set to zero, this value will be ignored and the cache will be disabled.
Controls whether the caching catalog will cache table entries using case sensitive keys.
Controls the duration for which entries in the catalog are cached.
Behavior of specific values of cache.expiration-interval-ms:

listitem.para: Zero - Caching and cache expiration are both disabled
Negative Values - Cache expiration is turned off and entries expire only on refresh etc
Positive Values - Cache entries expire if not accessed via the cache after this many milliseconds

detaileddescription.para: Controls whether to use caching during manifest reads or not.
Enabling manifest file caching require the following configuration constraints to be true:

listitem.para: IO_MANIFEST_CACHE_EXPIRATION_INTERVAL_MS must be a non-negative value.
IO_MANIFEST_CACHE_MAX_TOTAL_BYTES must be a positive value.
IO_MANIFEST_CACHE_MAX_CONTENT_LENGTH must be a positive value.

detaileddescription.para: Controls the maximum duration for which an entry stays in the manifest cache.
Must be a non-negative value. Following are specific behaviors of this config:

listitem.para: Zero - Cache entries expires only if it gets evicted due to memory pressure from {} setting. Positive Values - Cache entries expire if not accessed via the cache after this many milliseconds

detaileddescription.para: Controls the maximum total amount of bytes to cache in manifest cache.
Controls the maximum length of file to be considered for caching.
An org.apache.iceberg.io.InputFile will not be cached if the length is longer than this limit. Must be a positive value.
A comma separated list of elements used, in addition to the URI, to compose the key of the client pool cache.
Supported key elements in a Catalog are implementation-dependent.
